7 If the ambassador use armed force, he may undoubtedly be killed, not in the way of punishment, but in the way of natural defense. Thus the Fabii, whom Livy calls the violators of human law, might be killed by the Gauls. So in Euripides, Demophon threatcns the Hcrald. The name of this Herald was Copreus, and because he used violence, he was put to death by the Athenians, as Philostratus relates.
